    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-08-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-08-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="235"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d235">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/1032.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-08-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 10, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>It is the opinion of the six ministers that in view of rumors of loans to China
                    uniform action is desirable, and that in case the Foreign Office notifies a
                    minister that any of his nationals have made a loan approved by the Central
                    Government and requests the minister to take note and inform his nationals
                    concerned thereof, if such loan be upon other conditions than those already
                    approved by the six powers the minister shall reply in writing that he can not
                    act as requested because the loan is not based upon the conditions approved by
                    his Government. Has this the approval of the Department?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Calhoun.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
